# Repository Context Loading

Context loading is **not optional** — it is the first step before any work in this repository.

All agents and contributors must:
- understand the governance chain
- load required documentation
- respect constraint boundaries
- follow precedence rules

---

# 1. Mandatory Loading Order

## Before ANY Changes

Read these in order:

1. `CONTEXT.md` — mandatory loading order and precedence chain
2. `AGENTS.md` — complete development rules and constraints
3. All mandatory `docs/` from CONTEXT.md items 5–10:
   - `docs/GOVERNANCE.md`
   - `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
   - `docs/TESTING.md`
   - `docs/COMMENTS.md`
   - `docs/PLATFORMS.md`
   - `docs/DEPENDENCIES.md`
   - `docs/SECURITY.md`
   - `docs/RELEASES.md`

---

## MUST

- [ ] read `CONTEXT.md` first
- [ ] read `AGENTS.md` second
- [ ] read ALL mandatory docs above, not only those that seem relevant

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ skip context loading
- ❌ selectively read only "relevant" docs
- ❌ assume familiarity replaces reading
- ❌ begin changes before loading is complete

---

# 2. Source-of-Truth Precedence

When documents conflict, higher-precedence wins:

| Priority | Source |
|----------|--------|
| 1 | `CONTEXT.md` |
| 2 | `docs/GOVERNANCE.md` |
| 3 | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| 4 | Feature-specific documentation |
| 5 | Inline code comments |

---

## Rule

> If two sources disagree, follow the higher-precedence source and flag the conflict.

---

# 3. Non-Negotiable Constraints

These constraints are **absolute** — no exceptions without human approval.

## Architecture

- [ ] feature-first monorepo with `presentation → domain ← data` separation
- [ ] dependency direction: `presentation → domain ← data`
- [ ] features MUST NOT import from other features

---

## State & Navigation

- [ ] Riverpod only (no Provider, Redux, BLoC)
- [ ] go_router only for navigation
- [ ] no business logic in widgets
- [ ] no mutable shared state

---

## Type Safety & Immutability

- [ ] Dart null safety always enabled
- [ ] immutable models via freezed
- [ ] strict typing enforced (no untyped `dynamic` abuse)

---

## Generated Code

- [ ] never edit generated files (`*.g.dart`, `*.freezed.dart`, `*.gr.dart`)
- [ ] run `make gen` to regenerate
- [ ] run `make gen-check` to verify freshness

---

# 4. Quality Gate

## Required Before Committing

```bash
make preflight
```

This validates:
- formatting
- static analysis
- tests
- codegen consistency

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ commit without passing preflight
- ❌ skip tests or analysis
- ❌ bypass pre-commit hooks

---

